# UX Design Standards

## Golden Rule: Consistency is King

**Every screen with lists should follow the standard UX patterns.**

Reference: `docs/design/ux-patterns.md`

---

## The 7 Standard Patterns

When building ANY list or management screen, include:

### 1. **Search/Filter Bar** (if 10+ items expected)
```tsx
const [searchQuery, setSearchQuery] = useState('');

// At top of screen, below header
<View style={styles.searchContainer}>
  <TextInput
    value={searchQuery}
    onChangeText={setSearchQuery}
    placeholder="🔍 Search..."
  />
  {searchQuery && (
    <TouchableOpacity onPress={() => setSearchQuery('')}>
      <Text>✕</Text>
    </TouchableOpacity>
  )}
</View>
```

### 2. **Collapsible Groups** (if content is grouped)
```tsx
const [collapsedSections, setCollapsedSections] = useState<Set<string>>(new Set());

// Tap header to expand/collapse
<TouchableOpacity onPress={() => toggleSection(id)}>
  <View style={styles.sectionHeader}>
    <Text>{title}</Text>
    <Text>{collapsed ? '▶' : '▼'}</Text>
  </View>
</TouchableOpacity>
```

### 3. **Icon Buttons** (not text-only)
```tsx
// Use emoji icons for actions
<TouchableOpacity onPress={handleEdit}>
  <Text style={{ fontSize: 20 }}>✏️</Text>
</TouchableOpacity>
<TouchableOpacity onPress={handleDelete}>
  <Text style={{ fontSize: 20 }}>🗑️</Text>
</TouchableOpacity>
```

**Standard Icons**:
- ✏️ Edit
- 🗑️ Delete
- ➕ Add
- ✅ Confirm
- ✕ Cancel
- ⚙️ Settings

### 4. **Empty States** (always)
```tsx
{items.length === 0 && (
  <View style={styles.emptyState}>
    <Text style={styles.emptyIcon}>📋</Text>
    <Text style={styles.emptyTitle}>No Items Yet</Text>
    <Text style={styles.emptyDescription}>
      Helpful guidance on what to do next
    </Text>
    <PrimaryButton title="+ Add" onPress={handleAdd} />
  </View>
)}
```

### 5. **Count Badges** (on group headers)
```tsx
<Text style={styles.groupName}>
  Housing 
  <Text style={styles.countBadge}> ({items.length})</Text>
</Text>
```

### 6. **Status Indicators** (if items have states)
```tsx
{isActive && (
  <View style={[styles.badge, { backgroundColor: theme.status.success + '20' }]}>
    <Text style={{ color: theme.status.success }}>● Active</Text>
  </View>
)}
```

### 7. **Bulk Selection Mode** (if bulk actions make sense)
```tsx
const [selectionMode, setSelectionMode] = useState(false);
const [selectedItems, setSelectedItems] = useState<Set<string>>(new Set());

// Toggle button
<OutlineButton title="Select" onPress={() => setSelectionMode(true)} />

// Show checkboxes when in selection mode
{selectionMode && (
  <TouchableOpacity onPress={() => toggleSelection(id)}>
    <View style={styles.checkbox}>
      {selected && <Text>✓</Text>}
    </View>
  </TouchableOpacity>
)}
```

