## Implementation Checklist

Before marking a screen "complete":

- [ ] Has search bar (if 10+ items)
- [ ] Has collapsible groups (if grouped)
- [ ] Uses icon buttons (✏️🗑️ not "Edit" "Delete")
- [ ] Has empty state with guidance
- [ ] Has count badges on groups
- [ ] Has status indicators (if applicable)
- [ ] Has bulk selection (if bulk actions make sense)
- [ ] Uses SPACING constants
- [ ] Has loading state
- [ ] Has error states with retry

---

## Reference Implementation

**Example Screen**: `src/app/budget/manage-categories.tsx`

This screen demonstrates all 7 patterns perfectly. Use it as a template when creating new list screens.

---

## When to Deviate

**Only skip patterns if**:
- List is guaranteed to be < 5 items (no search needed)
- Content is not naturally grouped (no collapsible groups)
- Items have no actions (no buttons needed)
- Items have no states (no status indicators)

**Never skip**:
- Empty states (always required)
- Visual hierarchy (always required)
- Consistent spacing (always required)

---

## AI Assistant Rules

When generating a new list/management screen:

1. **Start with the checklist** - Go through all 7 patterns
2. **Copy from reference** - Use manage-categories.tsx as template
3. **Don't guess** - If unsure about a pattern, read docs/design/ux-patterns.md
4. **Ask about bulk actions** - Clarify if bulk operations make sense
5. **Test empty state** - Ensure it shows helpful guidance

### Bad Examples ❌

```tsx
// BAD: Text-only buttons
<TouchableOpacity>
  <Text>Edit</Text>
</TouchableOpacity>

// BAD: No empty state
{items.length === 0 ? null : <FlatList data={items} />}

// BAD: No search for long list
<FlatList data={allCategories} /> // 50+ items, no search!

// BAD: Always expanded groups
<Text>{groupName}</Text>
{items.map(item => <Card>{item.name}</Card>)}
```

### Good Examples ✅

```tsx
// GOOD: Icon button
<TouchableOpacity onPress={handleEdit}>
  <Text style={{ fontSize: 20 }}>✏️</Text>
</TouchableOpacity>

// GOOD: Empty state
{items.length === 0 && (
  <View style={styles.emptyState}>
    <Text style={styles.emptyIcon}>📋</Text>
    <Text style={styles.emptyTitle}>No Items</Text>
    <Text style={styles.emptyDescription}>Add your first item</Text>
    <PrimaryButton title="+ Add" onPress={handleAdd} />
  </View>
)}

// GOOD: Search + collapsible
<TextInput 
  value={searchQuery} 
  onChangeText={setSearchQuery}
  placeholder="🔍 Search..."
/>
<TouchableOpacity onPress={() => toggleGroup(id)}>
  <Text>{collapsed ? '▶' : '▼'} {groupName} ({count})</Text>
</TouchableOpacity>
```

